parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dashboard Cracking and Airbag Safety Concerns
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard around the airbag compartment can compromise the airbag's deployment speed and potentially cause fragmentation of the dashboard during deployment, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The dashboard is cracking around the passenger side airbag
the airbag indicator light is on or flashing
error messages appear on the dashboard
the airbag on/off indicator goes on and off when someone is sitting on the front passenger seat
the seatbelt warning signal starts ringing when the passenger removes their seatbelt and exits the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can cause the airbag to deploy incorrectly or not deploy at all, leading to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Error messages appear on the dashboard regarding the passenger airbag
the airbag on/off indicator goes on and off when someone is sitting on the front passenger seat
the seatbelt warning signal starts ringing when the passenger removes their seatbelt and exits the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to a delayed or incomplete braking response, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal hesitates or has a delayed response
the vehicle rolls forward when holding brakes at a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and peeling of the front dashboard can lead to a distraction while driving, potentially causing accidents, and may also reduce the overall value of the vehicle.
symptoms: Cracking and peeling of the front dashboard
potentially accompanied by a rough or uneven surface.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The "Not Ready" reading on the OBDII monitor for the catalyst inspection category can prevent the vehicle from passing smog checks, resulting in inconvenience and potential fines.
symptoms: OBDII monitor reads "Not Ready" for the catalyst inspection category
preventing the vehicle from passing smog checks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the transmission cooler lines can cause fluid leaks, leading to transmission damage and potentially causing accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaks
corrosion of the transmission cooler lines
potentially accompanied by signs of transmission failure such as slipping or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Hesitation and Failure to Accelerate
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation or failure of the vehicle to accelerate can cause accidents, especially when merging into traffic, crossing intersections, or making turns, as it can lead to sudden stops or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate when depressing the accelerator pedal
especially when slowing down or coming to a stop
causing the vehicle to jerk or vibrate; the vehicle may not engage gears automatically; the steering wheel may vibrate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Hunting for Gears and Jerking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission's failure to smoothly shift gears can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially when merging into traffic, crossing intersections, or making turns.
symptoms: The transmission hunts for gears
causing the vehicle to jerk or hesitate; the vehicle may vibrate or shudder when shifting gears; the vehicle may hesitate to accelerate when depressing the accelerator pedal.
